Antonio Sabàto Jr. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Sab%C3%A0to_Jr. 0 Antonio Sabàto Jr. (born February 29, 1972) is an Italian-American model, actor, and failed aspiring politician. Sabàto first found fame in the 1990s, posing as an underwear model for Calvin Klein and appearing as Jagger Cates on the soap opera General Hospital from 1992 to 1995. By the early 2000s, Sabàto's career had started to wane, most of his acting credits attributed to guest appearances, reality TV, and low budget films. In recent years, Sabàto has received attention in the media for his involvement in politics. He ran unsuccessfully for U.S. Congress against incumbent Democratic Congresswoman Julia Brownley for California's 26th district in the 2018 elections.
